Description: Fragment of handle-plate, handle and neck of East Greek pottery column-krater; inside of neck glazed with added red band lined in white; maeander band on top of rim; fat rays on handle-plate; edges of plate, outside of handle and neck glazed; graffito on top of rim.
Curator's comments: From same vessel as 1965,0930.715 & 716. Marked '12' in pencil.
Bibliographic references: Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG1041)
